Things are going... okay. Not gonna say it‚Äôs going great, but nonetheless. Still in my junior year of high school, and activities/sports have just gotten completely canceled for this chunk of the year, as cases have skyrocketed and virtual schooling is mandatory. As of these past weeks, I‚Äôve gotten closer with my best friend, Claire, and after years of sitting alone at lunch, it‚Äôs something I‚Äôve needed for a while. I think I‚Äôm actually getting somewhere in life and not just sitting on Discord all day. author: Sebastien Decuyper
text:
Checkpoint ;

To the surprise of absolutely no one, this year has been extremely rough. I've lost most of my friends, basically had to change country, wasted a year and thousands of euros because of a bunch of very ill-intended people.
I kinda know what I want to do with my life, but future is so scary. I'm scared to be a failure, to not achieve success in the way many of my role models did. 

I'm terrified. 
I'm trying to be optimistic, but it's hard. 
I'm trying to make friends, but it looks impossible.
I'm trying to do good around me, but everything is falling apart.

Let 2020 end already. I'm ready to move on something else.

author: main character
text:
I wouldn't say there's anything weird about this channel per se, it just is somebody who uploads songs from the soundtracks of Donkey Kong Country and Donkey Kong Country 2.  The weird thing is the fact that its getting randomly recommended to hundreds of thousands of people, even millions for some videos, whether or not they've even listened to these songs in their life. 

Due to this, this channel's video's have become a sort of refuge from the rest of the internet. (Heck, might as well be the rest of the world.) You'll see lots of people posting "checkpoints" which are basically updates on how their life has been so far. Doesn't matter who you are, or how lifes treating you, everybody here is willing to support you and keep you going. Thats why this channel is so great to me. Such a refresher from the rest of the toxic world. 

You should feel special! If these videos are being recommended to you, you're officially a main character of your own life. Just enjoy the music, and enjoy the company!

author: Tissue Box
text:
Checkpoint
August 6, 2020
12:26 AM

Not much to write up since my last visit to one of these videos two months ago, but what's present is good news. I feel better about myself than when I last wrote. Beating my new favorite game, Xenoblade Chronicles Definitive Edition, was not only a blast, it also got me thinking about life and the impact I have as an individual. My mom managed to close her restaurant, so almost all the arguing I mentioned last time has ceased, and nights are more peaceful. One day I worked up the courage to tell her, and my brother who overheard and joined in, about the depressive thoughts I've had for the first half of 2020. It was an ugly, yet cleansing experience for me releasing all that negativity from my system, but I couldn't be more glad that I did it. Everyone has dark and uncertain periods in their life, but they are a great opportunity for self improvement.

The big question for me now is how much I've improved. I start my senior year of high school in one week, but my homework isn't finished, I've been slacking on college research, and my future beyond that isn't much clearer than it was before. Plus with the stress of school, there's a chance my newfound positivity could be weakened or crushed. At the very least, I'll face these problems with more energy and purpose than before

author: Nickolias
text:
Take a seat. We've got all the time in the world. Well, actually we only have about fifteen minutes. But why's a number like that matter when we're here together.
Relax, listen to the music around you. You'll get sick of it eventually so it's best to enjoy it as much as you can now. And when you've had your fill, go back out into the world. And once you've had your fill of the world, come back here and listen to a new song.
I'll be back here some day, I'm sure of it. "When?" I couldn't tell you. It could be a week, it could be ten years. I just know that I keep ending up in this place. Because that's the kind of place it is: one that always draws you back. So best to enjoy the time you spend in it, since you don't know how long it'll be until you return.
Well, I best get going. The music is beginning to sound repetetive.
